The Crowbill <br/>
<br/>
Average Length: Approx. <br/>
<br/>
Type of Weapon: Distanced Hand-to-hand.<br/>
<br/>
<br/>
The crowbill is the weapon the fighting pick, named for its resemblance<br/>
to the bill of a crow. The most elaborate and best crafted weapons of<br/>
the crowbill type were from Persia and India. The crowbill and similar<br/>
picks were designed specifically to pierce through chain mail armor and<br/>
plate mail joints. <br/>
